2788/files/Understanding_the_Care_Certificate_-_number_of_standards_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692798340 320w" width="2000" height="1125" alt="Understanding the Care Certificate - number of standards - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Understanding the Care Certificate - number of standards - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-31_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-32_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-34_">Before we delve into the specifics of the Care Certificate, let's define what it is and why it matters. The Care Certificate is designed for the non-regulated health and social care workforce, ensuring that everyone has the same foundational skills, knowledge, and behaviours required to provide quality care and support. The Certificate, developed by a partnership between Health Education England, Skills for Health and Skills for Care, establishes a set of standards for health and social care workers. It has been deemed the benchmark for induction by the Care Quality Commission (CQC), ensuring a baseline of skills and knowledge. </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-35_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-37_">The structure of the Care Certificate </span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_structure_of_the_Care_Certificate_-_train_the_trainer_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692798425" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_structure_of_the_Care_Certificate_-_train_the_trainer_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692798425 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_structure_of_the_Care_Certificate_-_train_the_trainer_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692798425 320w" width="1872" height="1248" alt="The structure of the Care Certificate - train the trainer - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="The structure of the Care Certificate - train the trainer - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-38_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-39_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-41_">The Care Certificate consists of a set of fifteen minimum standards, each focusing on a specific area of knowledge or skill required in the health and social care sector. These fifteen standards include: </span></p><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-42_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-43_"><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-44_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-45_">Understand your role</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-47_">Your personal development</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-49_">Duty of care</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-51_">Equality and diversity</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-53_">Work in a person-centred way</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-55_">Communication</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-57_">Privacy and dignity</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-59_">Fluids and nutrition</li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-61_"><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-62_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-63_">9.&nbsp;Awareness of mental health, dementia, and learning disabilities</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-65_">10.&nbsp;Safeguarding adults and children</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-67_">11.&nbsp;Basic life support</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-69_">12.&nbsp;Health and safety</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-71_">13.&nbsp;Handling information</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-73_">14.&nbsp;Infection prevention and control</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-75_">15.&nbsp;Dementia Awareness</li></ul></div></div></div><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-77_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-79_">Emphasising the importance of each standard</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Emphasising_the_importance_of_each_standard_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692798518" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Emphasising_the_importance_of_each_standard_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692798518 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Emphasising_the_importance_of_each_standard_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692798518 320w" width="1900" height="1267" alt="Emphasising the importance of each standard - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Emphasising the importance of each standard - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-80_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-81_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-83_">Each standard included in the Care Certificate is vital in ensuring quality care and support. Understanding one's role, for example, is crucial in establishing a strong foundation for effective care provision. Promoting equality and diversity ensures that individuals from diverse backgrounds receive equal access to care and support. Person-centred care places the individual at the heart of their care journey, while effective communication fosters collaboration and trust. Duty of care is a legal requirement. Safeguarding adults and children is critical in the health and social care sector, protecting vulnerable individuals from abuse and harm. These are just a few examples of how each standard plays a vital role in ensuring quality care and support.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-84_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-86_">Training of the Care Certificate</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Training_of_the_Care_Certificate_-_train_the_trainer_pack_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_8d0534cf-e0d8-4357-8675-e705b7b0e66a.jpg?v=1692798646" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Training_of_the_Care_Certificate_-_train_the_trainer_pack_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_8d0534cf-e0d8-4357-8675-e705b7b0e66a.jpg?v=1692798646 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Training_of_the_Care_Certificate_-_train_the_trainer_pack_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_8d0534cf-e0d8-4357-8675-e705b7b0e66a_500x.jpg?v=1692798646 320w" width="2240" height="1493" alt="Training of the Care Certificate - train the trainer pack - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Training of the Care Certificate - train the trainer pack - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-87_"/><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-88_" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Becoming a trainer of the Care Certificate offers the opportunity to make a difference, share expertise, enhance career prospects and contribute to the growth of the health and social care sector. If you’re looking to train your new staff an